25|$|From 1986 to 2014, Scott {{served as}} the Executive Director of the National Center for Science Education, Inc., a nonprofit science {{education}} organization supporting teaching of evolutionary science. She holds a Ph.D. in biological anthropology from the University of Missouri. A biologist, her research has been in human medical anthropology and skeletal biology. Scott serves on the National Advisory Council of <b>Americans</b> <b>United</b> <b>for</b> Separation of Church and State.|$|E
